3
00:01:17,289 --> 00:01:21,380
[Episode 24]

4
00:01:18,860 --> 00:01:20,920
I can only care about my son secretly.

5
00:01:22,410 --> 00:01:25,060
But even with such deep longing for you,

6
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:29,380
I still resolutely refuse to admit my mistakes.

7
00:01:29,620 --> 00:01:31,020
Because I always thought

8
00:01:32,250 --> 00:01:33,759
that one day you would understand

9
00:01:33,759 --> 00:01:35,490
my good intentions as a father.

10
00:01:41,410 --> 00:01:41,970
Son.

11
00:01:44,630 --> 00:01:45,400
I was wrong.

12
00:01:48,890 --> 00:01:49,640
I'm sorry.

13
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,610
My stubbornness as a father

14
00:01:55,660 --> 00:01:57,660
has made us miss out on so many years.

15
00:01:59,770 --> 00:02:00,590
I'm sorry.

16
00:02:03,450 --> 00:02:04,950
I shouldn't have left you alone

17
00:02:04,950 --> 00:02:06,480
with your mother back then.

18
00:02:07,770 --> 00:02:10,139
I didn't notice your unease and sadness.

19
00:02:11,480 --> 00:02:12,280
I'm sorry.

20
00:02:13,260 --> 00:02:17,120
I believed that family wealth is the most important protective tool.

21
00:02:17,450 --> 00:02:19,300
But I made you and your mother

22
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:22,440
have irreparable regrets.

23
00:02:27,660 --> 00:02:28,570
I was wrong.

24
00:02:31,180 --> 00:02:32,340
I was really wrong.

25
00:02:36,740 --> 00:02:37,370
Haikuo.

26
00:02:40,570 --> 00:02:42,510
You don't need to choose

27
00:02:42,540 --> 00:02:44,070
between me and your mother.

28
00:02:46,490 --> 00:02:48,690
Because you are the motivation and hope

29
00:02:48,970 --> 00:02:49,700
of our lives.

30
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:11,700
This is a letter your mother left for me.

31
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:26,560
She probably had an intuition in her heart.

32
00:03:27,590 --> 00:03:30,690
She knew she wouldn't be able to see me before she passed away.

33
00:03:30,690 --> 00:03:32,350
So she wrote this letter to me.

34
00:03:34,170 --> 00:03:35,340
I thought

35
00:03:37,490 --> 00:03:38,880
she would blame me

36
00:03:39,590 --> 00:03:40,390
and resent me.

37
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:42,800
But in her letter,

38
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,610
every word

39
00:03:45,510 --> 00:03:46,540
was reminding me,

40
00:03:48,670 --> 00:03:50,329
telling me not to stay up late,

41
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:53,520
not to be so busy that I forget to eat,

42
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:56,090
and not to eat liver foods

43
00:03:57,440 --> 00:04:00,570
because she was afraid my cholesterol would be too high.

44
00:04:01,190 --> 00:04:02,720
She told me to watch my diet.

45
00:04:08,150 --> 00:04:09,410
She was just that good,

46
00:04:11,870 --> 00:04:13,130
always so gentle.

47
00:04:15,370 --> 00:04:16,170
That's right.

48
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:19,700
She was the person who treated me

49
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:20,959
the best in this world.

50
00:04:23,140 --> 00:04:24,070
She loved me.

51
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,310
She forgave me.

52
00:04:27,910 --> 00:04:30,710
She always thought about me in everything she did.

53
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:32,670
But...

54
00:04:35,980 --> 00:04:38,370
But I didn't go to see her one last time.

55
00:04:50,650 --> 00:04:51,420
I'm sorry.

56
00:04:53,950 --> 00:04:54,570
Kid.

57
00:04:57,250 --> 00:04:59,310
Don't make the same mistakes as I did.

58
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:03,360
What do you mean?

59
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,840
I know you broke up with Keke.

60
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:14,030
After you broke up,

61
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:16,840
Keke came to see me.

62
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:25,170
She still defended you,

63
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:27,350
spoke for you,

64
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:28,820
and blamed me for you.

65
00:05:31,580 --> 00:05:32,659
So I hope

66
00:05:35,380 --> 00:05:37,440
you won't have the same regrets as me,

67
00:05:39,860 --> 00:05:42,120
losing the person who loves you the most.

68
00:05:55,820 --> 00:05:57,720
I'm the manager of the Business Department?

69
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:58,310
Yes.

70
00:05:58,950 --> 00:06:01,030
Ellly's cousin is the HR manager.

71
00:06:01,290 --> 00:06:02,030
He said that.

72
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:04,050
The HR order will be issued soon.

73
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:06,760
How is that possible?

74
00:06:07,220 --> 00:06:08,220
How could it be me?

75
00:06:09,050 --> 00:06:09,700
Why?

76
00:06:11,950 --> 00:06:13,470
A big client who is about to sign

77
00:06:13,470 --> 00:06:16,180
a long-term cooperation deal with us.

78
00:06:16,350 --> 00:06:17,320
Their superior specified

79
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:19,450
that you should be the contact person.

80
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:25,250
Is the big client you just mentioned

81
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:27,010
Haikuo's father's company?

82
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,900
Yes.

83
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:31,370
Strange.

84
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:34,420
Why would President Wang specify me?

85
00:06:35,540 --> 00:06:37,540
Could it be to make up for something?

86
00:06:43,940 --> 00:06:45,110
I'm sorry.

87
00:06:46,020 --> 00:06:47,950
Are you trying to harm me secretly?

88
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:52,550
Keke.

89
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:54,600
You really keep your word.

90
00:06:54,850 --> 00:06:56,620
President Wang has already agreed to cooperate.

91
00:06:56,620 --> 00:06:58,820
He's ready to sign the contract with us.

92
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:00,540
Really?

93
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:02,010
Of course, it's true.

94
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:03,320
His representative will be here shortly

95
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:04,520
to sign the contract.

96
00:07:04,860 --> 00:07:05,610
Keke.

97
00:07:05,830 --> 00:07:08,290
You are really the lucky star of our company.

98
00:07:08,730 --> 00:07:09,870
You are the savior.

99
00:07:09,890 --> 00:07:10,610
Savior.

100
00:07:13,180 --> 00:07:14,960
I don't think I did anything.

101
00:07:14,990 --> 00:07:18,000
I was surprised that they decided to sign the contract.

102
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,080
If it weren't for you,

103
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:20,810
why would President Wang

104
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:21,850
name you

105
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:23,910
as the representative for signing the contract?

106
00:07:23,910 --> 00:07:24,880
Me as the representative?

107
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:26,710
I'm not even in the Business Department.

108
00:07:26,710 --> 00:07:27,980
As long as we can sign the contract,

109
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:29,260
everything's fine.

110
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:34,330
General Manager, the representative from TV Group is here.

111
00:07:34,330 --> 00:07:35,930
Good, please let them in.

112
00:07:35,970 --> 00:07:36,510
Come in.

113
00:07:52,460 --> 00:07:53,240
Haikuo?

114
00:07:58,930 --> 00:07:59,530
Hello.

115
00:07:59,830 --> 00:08:02,230
I represent President Wang Changfa of TV Group

116
00:08:02,230 --> 00:08:04,040
to discuss our cooperation.

117
00:08:05,130 --> 00:08:08,190
You represent President Wang to discuss the contract?

118
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,290
Please, have a seat.

119
00:08:13,290 --> 00:08:13,900
Thank you.

120
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:20,650
Have some tea.

121
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:21,840
Thank you.

122
00:08:23,850 --> 00:08:24,930
Keke, have a seat.

123
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:27,010
Here, have some tea.

124
00:08:28,460 --> 00:08:29,450
But, General Manager,

125
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:30,560
I'm from the Accounting Department.

126
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:33,350
I'm really not familiar with the details of the business.

127
00:08:33,350 --> 00:08:34,760
You handle the signing.

128
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,059
For the follow-up,

129
00:08:36,059 --> 00:08:39,030
I'll have Sales Manager Chen Shi of Division One assist you.

130
00:08:39,030 --> 00:08:41,559
Chen Shi is the Sales Manager of Division One?

131
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:43,350
General Manager, this arrangement

132
00:08:43,350 --> 00:08:44,340
is really great.

133
00:08:45,740 --> 00:08:46,320
Well.

134
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,360
General Manager.

135
00:08:47,460 --> 00:08:48,660
This means I'll have to do

136
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:49,520
two jobs,

137
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:50,920
but only get paid for one.

138
00:08:56,780 --> 00:08:58,190
If you do two jobs,

139
00:08:58,190 --> 00:08:58,780
well,

140
00:08:58,950 --> 00:09:01,150
of course, you'll get paid for two jobs.

141
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:02,340
Well...

142
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:07,110
Here, have some tea.

143
00:09:07,140 --> 00:09:07,840
Thank you.

144
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:10,730
You all planned this, didn't you?

145
00:09:12,210 --> 00:09:13,380
Brilliant move.

146
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:14,890
You caught Keke off guard.

147
00:09:14,890 --> 00:09:16,610
Keke must be surprised out of her wits.

148
00:09:16,610 --> 00:09:17,570
More than Keke,

149
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:19,550
I was also surprised out of my wits.

150
00:09:19,750 --> 00:09:22,300
The workload will increase now.

151
00:09:23,180 --> 00:09:24,170
Keke's work

152
00:09:24,220 --> 00:09:25,860
won't just be shared with you.

153
00:09:25,860 --> 00:09:26,990
Why are you sighing?

154
00:09:27,150 --> 00:09:28,930
But the parts Keke is responsible for

155
00:09:28,930 --> 00:09:30,190
are more complicated.

156
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:32,490
It's just the Business Department's documents.

157
00:09:32,490 --> 00:09:34,290
I'll help you with the accounts.

158
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:35,890
But this means

159
00:09:35,890 --> 00:09:37,150
you can't leave work on time.

160
00:09:37,150 --> 00:09:38,610
You have to work overtime.

161
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:39,950
Overtime is fine.

162
00:09:40,290 --> 00:09:42,110
I can get paid for overtime.

163
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:43,310
Making more money

164
00:09:43,350 --> 00:09:45,480
can increase our house purchase fund.

165
00:09:49,890 --> 00:09:52,550
Since you represent President Wang's company,

166
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:55,210
does this mean you've reconciled with your dad?

167
00:09:57,250 --> 00:09:58,280
It's hard to say.

168
00:09:58,690 --> 00:09:59,820
But now we have

169
00:09:59,820 --> 00:10:01,820
a regular monthly dinner together.

170
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:05,130
So what's your arrangement with me and Keke

171
00:10:05,130 --> 00:10:06,180
supposed to mean?

172
00:10:06,620 --> 00:10:08,000
Isn't it obvious?

173
00:10:08,220 --> 00:10:10,420
He wants to get back together with Keke.

174
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,220
Manager Chen.

175
00:10:15,470 --> 00:10:16,720
I'm May from the Planning Department.

176
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:18,130
This drink is buy one get one free.

177
00:10:18,130 --> 00:10:19,190
Here's one for you.

178
00:10:28,850 --> 00:10:30,190
That's impressive.

179
00:10:30,490 --> 00:10:32,150
You're quite lucky with the ladies.

180
00:10:32,150 --> 00:10:33,950
Someone even bought you a drink.

181
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,070
It looks like Chen Shi

182
00:10:36,430 --> 00:10:38,430
might get into a relationship soon.

183
00:10:39,490 --> 00:10:40,820
Congratulations.

184
00:10:40,850 --> 00:10:41,990
Congratulations.

185
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:46,250
Yu Fen.

186
00:10:46,830 --> 00:10:47,890
What are you doing?

187
00:10:58,470 --> 00:10:59,020
Mi.

188
00:10:59,070 --> 00:10:59,890
Can you take

189
00:10:59,890 --> 00:11:01,950
three days of annual leave next week?

190
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:03,150
Sure.

191
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:04,370
Why?

192
00:11:05,220 --> 00:11:07,050
My parents know we're dating.

193
00:11:07,090 --> 00:11:09,320
So they want me to take you back to Singapore

194
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,270
to meet them.

195
00:11:16,310 --> 00:11:16,990
Okay?

196
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:25,180
Yu Fen.

197
00:11:25,930 --> 00:11:26,940
My mom said

198
00:11:27,140 --> 00:11:28,740
we shouldn't play with food.

199
00:11:45,860 --> 00:11:48,220
Although we haven't really started making money yet,

200
00:11:48,220 --> 00:11:49,730
we're almost breaking even.

201
00:11:49,730 --> 00:11:51,260
I think in a few more months,

202
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,480
we'll be in the black.

203
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,670
That's pretty soon.

204
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:06,820
What's wrong?

205
00:12:07,910 --> 00:12:09,700
My mom messaged me.

206
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:10,590
She said

207
00:12:10,770 --> 00:12:12,370
she wants to meet me tomorrow

208
00:12:12,590 --> 00:12:14,250
to give me the money in person.

209
00:12:15,290 --> 00:12:16,660
Why go to all that trouble?

210
00:12:16,660 --> 00:12:19,460
She could just transfer the money to your account.

211
00:12:20,820 --> 00:12:22,390
Are you going to see her?

212
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:27,220
You have to run the business.

213
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:29,150
How do you have time during the day?

214
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:34,960
I should meet her anyway.

215
00:12:51,090 --> 00:12:52,300
I'm sorry.

216
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,400
It's okay.

217
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:57,880
Yu Fen.

218
00:12:59,570 --> 00:13:01,220
Are you free tonight?

219
00:13:02,390 --> 00:13:03,280
Would you like

220
00:13:03,730 --> 00:13:05,130
to have dinner together?

221
00:13:17,820 --> 00:13:18,850
Manager Chen.

222
00:13:21,810 --> 00:13:23,240
Manager Chen, let me help you pick it up.

223
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:23,990
No.

224
00:13:25,150 --> 00:13:26,750
It's fine, I'll do it myself.

225
00:13:26,770 --> 00:13:27,920
I dropped it myself.

226
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:33,680
Yu Fen.

227
00:13:35,060 --> 00:13:35,860
Manager Chen.

228
00:13:35,910 --> 00:13:37,840
Can I have dinner with you tonight?

229
00:13:39,470 --> 00:13:40,700
I just remembered

230
00:13:40,730 --> 00:13:41,920
I have something to do tonight.

231
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:42,970
I'll leave now.

232
00:13:43,050 --> 00:13:43,980
What about tomorrow?

233
00:13:43,980 --> 00:13:44,910
I'm free tomorrow.

234
00:13:44,910 --> 00:13:46,790
If not tomorrow, the day after is also fine.

235
00:13:46,790 --> 00:13:47,660
Manager Chen.

236
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:53,840
Jiali.

237
00:13:54,250 --> 00:13:54,820
Mom.

238
00:14:00,580 --> 00:14:01,210
This

239
00:14:01,830 --> 00:14:03,490
is to repay the money I owe you.

240
00:14:10,210 --> 00:14:11,810
Aren't you going to count it?

241
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:13,040
It's okay.

242
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:13,890
No need.

243
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:20,420
Is there something we need to meet about?

244
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:22,550
You should open it and check.

245
00:14:23,730 --> 00:14:24,510
Count it.

246
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:28,490
Okay.

247
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:43,890
What's in the paper bag?

248
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,330
I don't know.

249
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:47,400
But Jiali looks shocked.

250
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:49,820
Could it be fake money?

251
00:14:50,490 --> 00:14:51,350
Fake money?

252
00:14:51,620 --> 00:14:52,350
No way.

253
00:14:52,390 --> 00:14:53,600
I need to go check.

254
00:14:54,540 --> 00:14:55,860
Grandma, no.

255
00:14:56,970 --> 00:14:58,230
You'll be discovered.

256
00:15:06,660 --> 00:15:09,260
I remember you liked this photo a lot.

257
00:15:09,790 --> 00:15:11,100
I found the negatives.

258
00:15:11,130 --> 00:15:13,190
So I had it printed for you.

259
00:15:39,380 --> 00:15:40,060
Mom.

260
00:16:01,530 --> 00:16:02,960
What's going on now?

261
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:05,170
I don't know.

262
00:16:06,620 --> 00:16:09,020
Jiali, I'm sorry.

263
00:16:10,420 --> 00:16:12,330
I know I've been selfish.

264
00:16:13,650 --> 00:16:15,200
Can you forgive me?

265
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:27,030
Can I come visit you often from now on?

266
00:16:27,970 --> 00:16:29,150
Of course.

267
00:16:30,610 --> 00:16:33,580
Look at you. You've grown so much.

268
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:38,820
It's hard to run a shop now.

269
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:40,430
Take good care of yourself.

270
00:16:40,450 --> 00:16:41,180
Got it?

271
00:16:41,570 --> 00:16:42,540
You too.

272
00:16:46,530 --> 00:16:48,310
I have something to do later.

273
00:16:48,750 --> 00:16:49,950
I have to go now.

274
00:16:49,980 --> 00:16:51,580
Remember to take your stuff.

275
00:16:56,570 --> 00:16:57,690
Keep in touch.

276
00:16:58,510 --> 00:16:59,650
Keep in touch.

277
00:17:00,810 --> 00:17:01,460
Bye.

278
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:12,240
Grandma.

279
00:17:12,510 --> 00:17:13,230
Jiali.

280
00:17:14,270 --> 00:17:15,599
What's in there?

281
00:17:15,619 --> 00:17:17,859
Grandma, why are you here?

282
00:17:23,390 --> 00:17:24,530
It's this.

283
00:17:28,630 --> 00:17:31,160
Isn't this your most cherished family photo?

284
00:17:32,630 --> 00:17:34,490
She said she found the negatives.

285
00:17:34,590 --> 00:17:36,370
So she printed one for me.

286
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:39,810
She also apologized to me just now.

287
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:41,880
She said she knows she's been selfish.

288
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:43,410
She hopes I can forgive her.

289
00:17:43,930 --> 00:17:45,990
She also said we should keep in touch.

290
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:48,380
So,

291
00:17:48,620 --> 00:17:49,750
did you promise her?

